{
  "stem": "19969.7",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "The highest number I've seen is in a book I have here, it's I think 545.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] Well, that's far-fetched from 34.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "But other books also have equally high numbers of-- of German soldiers who were killed there.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "The true numbers is 34.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "I don't care if there were 500.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "If we had killed 500, I would say so.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] There's no reason for me to worry about how many were killed there.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "I-- but I was-- I was there.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And why they come-- I think a lot of these authors in order to embellish their book have to exaggerate their numbers.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "I find that quite common among authors who weren't there who are writing about historic events, they want to embellish their story.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "And I'm sure that's the case.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "Some of these books are more or less factual, but none of them are accurate.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] But anyway, I was always intrigued by all these books that said how many we had killed.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "And I knew it wasn't the case.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "But after-- immediately after the armistice was declared, which was about May 8, I guess officially it was, right-- a few days after Dachau, we started-- the American-- the Allied forces started rounding up all the SS officers because many were wanted for known atrocities-- the Malmedy massacre during the Battle of the Bulge where American soldiers were lined up and killed.",
      "word_count": 62
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "We had the names of some of those officers from witnesses, SS officers.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "You never found the regular German Army doing things like this.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "It was always the SS.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "And they were wanted for a great number of atrocities, so we rounded up all we could find and there were brought to Dachau.",
      "word_count": 24
    }
  ],
